@flouthoc is correct.

As the error message says `--cache-from` and `--cache-to` does not support `tags`.

@jwendell: Simply remove the `:master-latest-amd64`

Notice that Docker/BuildX supports static tags for those command line argument, allowing to dramatically reduce the storage footprint in the registry.
Podman/Buildah instead generates some random tag id.
